stylometry: With decision theories, there is a group of information that is used to make a decision. A payoff table is used in decision theory because there is information that is put into the table to help make the best decision. The components of a payoff table include the alternatives (all the choices you have), the state of nature (whether or not it is favorable or unfavorable) and the payoffs (what could you ultimately get). Each alternative has a probability of being favorable and a probablility of being unfavorable. These probablilities are then used to calculate the payoff of the decision. Payoff tables are not as good as decision trees because we cannot see the entire decsion making process and all of the possible decsions to be made at one time.
